      "flip_evidence_text": "The materiality standard is the explicit textual requirement that the event be a \"material event, fact, circumstance, development or occurrence\"; the requirement that the event be \"not known to, or reasonably foreseeable by, the Company Board\" is a separate knowledge and foreseeability qualifier, not the materiality standard.",
      "notes": "The claim correctly concludes that a materiality standard exists, but incorrectly identifies the \"not known to, or reasonably foreseeable by\" clause as that standard, rather than the explicit \"material\" qualifier at the beginning of the definition."
    }
  ]
}

